'''Munakata Shrine''' (宗像神社, Munakata-jinja) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Shiroi|ja|白井市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県|12=draft}}, in the {{ill|Kiyoto|ja|清戸|12=draft}} district.

== Enshrined Deities ==
* {{ill|Three Munakata Goddesses|ja|宗像三女神|1=Three Munakata Goddesses|1=Three Munakata Goddesses|qq=Three Munakata Goddesses|12=draft}}
** {{ill|Tagorihime|ja|田心姫神|12=draft}}
** {{ill|Ichikishima-hime|ja|市杵島姫神|12=draft}}
** 

== History ==
The shrine is said to have been established in {{ill|876|ja|876th year|12=draft}} ({{ill|Jōgan era|ja|貞観|12=draft}} 18). It was rebuilt in {{ill|1604|ja|1604th year|12=draft}} ({{ill|Keichō era|ja|慶長|12=draft}} 8) and again in {{ill|1831|ja|1831st year|12=draft}} ({{ill|Tenpō era|ja|天保|12=draft}} 2).

[[File:Munakata-shrine-torii-chiba-feb21-2016.jpg|thumb|Torii gate]]
== Overview ==
The shrine is regarded as the {{ill|Sōchinju|ja|総鎮守|12=draft}} (chief shrine) of the many Munakata shrines located around the southern edge of the northern plateau by {{ill|Inbanuma|ja|印旛沼|12=draft}}. It is believed to be the oldest shrine among the Munakata shrines in the region. 

Nearby are {{ill|Yakuō-ji (Shiroi)|ja|薬王寺 (白井市)|12=draft}}, associated with local dragon legends, and {{ill|Benzaiten (Shiroi)|ja|弁財天 (白井市)|12=draft}}.

== Access ==
Approximately a 25-minute walk from {{ill|Chiba New Town Chūō Station|ja|千葉ニュータウン中央駅|12=draft}}.

